        "## 3b. Sentiment data — Loughran-McDonald 10-K/10-Q tone (point-in-time)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Source.** Loughran-McDonald 10-X Summaries (SRAF, Notre Dame), per Ed post #34. The file\n",
        "is keyed by `CIK` + `FILING_DATE`, so we bridge tickers → CIK using the SEC's free\n",
        "`company_tickers.json`, then build five standardised tone features.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Leakage control (critical).** A filing is only public *after* its filing date, so we use\n",
        "an **as-of (point-in-time) merge**: each weekly panel date receives the most recent filing\n",
        "**strictly on or before** that date, forward-filled until the next filing. A 10-K dated\n",
        "2015-07-20 never influences any week before 2015-07-20.\n"
      ]
